WEBVTT

00:02.794 --> 00:06.378
NARRATOR: Three weeks ago,
a dome crashed on Chester's Mill,

00:06.548 --> 00:08.413
cutting us off
from the rest of the world.

00:09.176 --> 00:10.461
The dome has tested our limits,

00:11.178 --> 00:14.090
forcing each of us
to confront our own personal demons:

00:14.848 --> 00:15.883
Rage.

00:17.142 --> 00:18.678
Grief.

00:19.686 --> 00:21.642
- Fear.
- My God.

00:23.315 --> 00:24.430
Now in order to survive,

00:24.608 --> 00:27.520
we must battle
our most dangerous adversary:

00:27.986 --> 00:30.102
the enemy within.

00:31.532 --> 00:32.988
Do you remember
what we talked about?

00:33.158 --> 00:35.695
- What you need to do for Barbie?
- I'll do whatever it takes.

00:35.869 --> 00:37.700
Christine and Eva are using you.

00:37.871 --> 00:39.327
They want you to become like them.

00:39.498 --> 00:40.578
Barbie's not the same.

00:40.749 --> 00:42.785
- And Aktaion's all dead.
- We're on our own.

00:42.960 --> 00:44.666
SAM:
Abby!

00:46.129 --> 00:48.791
I'm sorry, but I'll never be able
to be who you want.

00:50.676 --> 00:52.667
NORRIE: What happened?
- l was supposed to meet Sam.

00:52.844 --> 00:55.005
Why should you forgive him?
He killed Angie.

00:55.180 --> 00:56.886
You should've told him
to go screw himself.

00:57.057 --> 00:58.137
This is you.

00:58.308 --> 00:59.718
You're back.

00:59.893 --> 01:03.101
Your fourth cervical vertebra
is fractured. You'd never walk again.

01:03.272 --> 01:05.684
If it's what's best,
then I want to do it.

01:05.857 --> 01:07.313
No.

01:07.484 --> 01:08.940
Let's get him the hell out of here.

01:09.945 --> 01:11.901
- What happened?
- Get me to the caves.

01:12.739 --> 01:14.070
Bring me Sam.

01:52.070 --> 01:53.480
[BODY THUDS]

01:57.367 --> 01:58.402
Hey. What are you--?

01:59.453 --> 02:00.533
Hey!

02:00.704 --> 02:01.944
EVA:
Dale! Dale, help!

02:02.122 --> 02:04.704
- Help!
- Eva! I'm on my way!

02:06.793 --> 02:08.579
EVA:
Please, don't do this. Dale!

02:11.798 --> 02:13.459
BARBIE:
Audrey, no!

02:17.262 --> 02:18.377
What the hell are you doing?

02:18.847 --> 02:20.178
There's no one to guide us.

02:21.224 --> 02:23.476
- I need tojump.
- Stop! You don't wanna do this.

02:23.644 --> 02:24.679
Stop!

02:47.084 --> 02:49.951
EVA: It's a shooting star.
- Those can't all be shooting stars.

02:52.089 --> 02:53.329
JULIA:
Here, boy. Indy.

02:53.507 --> 02:55.122
That all you got?

02:55.300 --> 02:56.756
Gotta put your gut into it.

02:56.927 --> 02:58.133
Indy!

02:58.303 --> 02:59.713
JULIA:
He's a dog. He can hear us.

02:59.888 --> 03:02.425
- I'm trying not to scare him away.
- lndy's not a liberal.

03:02.599 --> 03:05.011
He doesn't get scared of everything.

03:05.185 --> 03:07.471
- Indy!
- Indy!

03:07.646 --> 03:08.681
Indy--

03:09.690 --> 03:11.100
Pink stars?

03:11.274 --> 03:12.810
Oh, don't start with that crap again.

03:12.984 --> 03:14.975
Jim, look.

03:17.322 --> 03:19.028
What the hell?

03:19.783 --> 03:21.148
Shooting stars burn out.

03:23.120 --> 03:24.826
Did that starjust hit us?

03:33.004 --> 03:34.255
Oh, my God.

03:34.423 --> 03:36.414
JIM:
Looks like a meteor!

03:51.106 --> 03:53.688
BARBIE: At least the pink stars
seemed to calm everyone down.

03:54.192 --> 03:57.810
Audrey said there's no one to guide us.
She must have meant Christine.

03:57.988 --> 03:59.899
- Well, where is she?
- I don't know.

04:00.073 --> 04:01.358
But until she shows up,

04:01.533 --> 04:03.239
we have to make sure
the town stays safe.

04:03.410 --> 04:05.617
[DOME CREAKING]

04:06.538 --> 04:07.698
Was that the dome?

04:08.749 --> 04:10.580
Tell me it'll protect us
from the meteors.

04:10.751 --> 04:13.993
It held against the largest
nonnuclear ordnance the military has.

04:14.171 --> 04:16.503
A meteor impact
is thousands of times stronger.

04:16.673 --> 04:19.836
- Yes. It is.
- There must be something we can do.

04:20.010 --> 04:22.171
You're not one to sit around
and do nothing.

04:22.345 --> 04:25.303
Well, you got the fire tower.
That's got a view of the whole town.

04:25.474 --> 04:28.216
So I can survey the damage,
see if the dome held everywhere.

04:28.393 --> 04:30.634
- When do we leave?
- Whoa, we?

04:30.812 --> 04:33.224
If it's safe enough for you,
it's safe enough for me.

04:33.398 --> 04:36.060
Okay. So we go
to the fire marshal's office.

04:36.234 --> 04:39.146
We get the key,
key gets us access into the tower.

04:51.166 --> 04:52.576
"Rusty loves Linda."

04:52.751 --> 04:53.991
BARBIE:
Linda was our sheriff.

04:54.169 --> 04:57.536
She died
when the dome was magnetized.

05:09.976 --> 05:11.056
The dome held.

05:13.230 --> 05:15.221
BARBIE: I wonder
if this happened everywhere.

05:15.398 --> 05:18.014
You saw how many meteors
there were.

05:19.528 --> 05:21.143
- Some will survive.
- Yes.

05:21.321 --> 05:24.233
Some will survive the initial impact.

05:24.658 --> 05:26.649
But then the debris
that was kicked up into orbit,

05:26.827 --> 05:28.567
that'll rain down.

05:28.745 --> 05:31.077
And then the sun will disappear
behind a dust cloud,

05:31.248 --> 05:32.829
and then comes the firestorm.

05:32.999 --> 05:35.160
How do you know all this?

05:35.836 --> 05:38.953
I'm an anthropologist.
We study extinction-level events.

05:39.130 --> 05:41.166
- Well, you could be wrong.
- I could be.

05:41.967 --> 05:43.753
But I'm not.

05:50.976 --> 05:53.262
The debris is falling now.

05:58.900 --> 06:02.142
I always thought
the end would be caused by us.

06:03.071 --> 06:06.404
Nuclear war, global warming.

06:07.576 --> 06:10.443
The brick wall seen coming
but slammed into anyway.

06:11.496 --> 06:12.827
All those people.

06:13.456 --> 06:15.538
Billions of them.

06:17.043 --> 06:19.876
You know, we spent so much time

06:20.046 --> 06:22.378
trying to figure out
how to get out of this thing.

06:22.549 --> 06:26.918
And now, if we could only figure out
a way to get someone inside.

06:29.556 --> 06:30.796
The red door.

06:30.974 --> 06:32.430
- What?
- It's a way in.

06:32.601 --> 06:35.513
If we can get word out...
We gotta get to Bird Island.

06:35.687 --> 06:38.349
- Why do you wanna go to Bird Island?
- Aktaion's there.

06:38.523 --> 06:41.230
They had to be communicating
with the outside world.

06:41.610 --> 06:44.397
There is a way in, okay?
I know. I've been through it before.

06:44.571 --> 06:47.608
It's a long shot it's still standing,
but for anyone that's alive out there,

06:47.782 --> 06:50.649
- it's the only shot that they have.
- That might not be a good idea.

06:50.827 --> 06:52.658
- Eva, where's the key?
- What key?

06:53.413 --> 06:54.619
The key for the hatch.

06:54.789 --> 06:57.371
- I thought you had it.
- No, I stuck it right here.

06:57.542 --> 06:59.203
- Did it fall?
- Start looking.

06:59.377 --> 07:00.412
We gotta find the key.

07:12.057 --> 07:13.593
[METAL CLANGING
AND BARBIE GRUNTING]

07:13.767 --> 07:14.802
Damn it!

07:15.769 --> 07:18.260
Maybe it's a good thing we're stuck.

07:18.438 --> 07:19.553
How is that a good thing?

07:21.775 --> 07:24.141
If you were able to get a message
to the outside world,

07:24.319 --> 07:26.605
you and I both know
what would happen.

07:29.699 --> 07:31.815
It'd be chaos.

07:34.204 --> 07:37.071
People would do horrific things
to one another to get through that door.

07:37.248 --> 07:39.159
And those are the people
who would make it in.

07:39.584 --> 07:42.371
People like Big Jim. Or Julia.

07:42.796 --> 07:46.380
- People only interested in themselves.
- Well, we can deal with those people.

07:46.549 --> 07:48.631
The real problem
is how do you feed them?

07:48.802 --> 07:50.542
A thousand.

07:51.179 --> 07:52.680
Ten thousand
that would come through.

07:52.847 --> 07:54.758
Our resources
are already stretched thin.

07:54.933 --> 07:56.469
You're a good man, Dale.

07:56.643 --> 07:58.884
You wanna do what's right,
but look out there.

07:59.062 --> 08:00.677
This is no longer
about right or wrong.

08:00.855 --> 08:02.516
This is about survival.

08:02.691 --> 08:04.306
The survival of this town.

08:04.484 --> 08:06.850
Yeah, but you can't let everybody
on the outside just die

08:07.028 --> 08:09.440
without trying to do something.

08:11.533 --> 08:13.023
[SIGHS]

08:14.327 --> 08:16.283
So many burdens.

08:17.205 --> 08:19.662
So much weight on your shoulders.

08:23.420 --> 08:26.127
- It can all go away.
- What are you talking about?

08:29.175 --> 08:31.632
I'm talking about...

08:33.096 --> 08:35.257
no more worry,

08:35.765 --> 08:38.097
no more fear,

08:39.060 --> 08:41.016
no more doubt.

08:44.190 --> 08:46.306
You can be free like me.

08:48.653 --> 08:52.316
And in the process,
join something greater.

08:53.241 --> 08:55.323
You can evolve.

09:05.545 --> 09:07.706
Do you feel it, Dale?

09:10.633 --> 09:12.589
The pull?

09:15.805 --> 09:18.057
I know you can, just as I do.

09:19.601 --> 09:21.717
That's the kinship.

09:23.313 --> 09:25.554
There's harmony there.

09:26.107 --> 09:28.519
There's peace.

09:30.278 --> 09:32.018
Freedom.

09:35.033 --> 09:37.115
You'll still be you.

09:40.330 --> 09:43.868
With all your thoughts and desires.

09:55.428 --> 09:57.214
You still have desires, don't you?

10:01.434 --> 10:03.049
