Dale.

10:30.630 --> 10:33.872
NORRIE: Was that--?
- A meteor impact.

10:34.425 --> 10:38.043
Yeah, like the one that killed
all the dinosaurs.

10:38.221 --> 10:40.462
[DOME CREAKING]

10:41.766 --> 10:43.142
Is the dome cracking?

10:43.309 --> 10:45.015
HUNTER:
What the hell's going on?

10:47.105 --> 10:48.595
We don't know.

10:48.773 --> 10:50.684
But it's like an apocalypse out there.

10:50.859 --> 10:53.475
No. I meant,
why did you bring me here?

10:53.653 --> 10:56.144
- Eva was gonna kill you.
- But I wanted her to.

10:57.657 --> 10:59.113
How can you even say that?

10:59.284 --> 11:00.865
It's best for the kinship.

11:01.035 --> 11:02.741
I'm using up all the pain medication.

11:02.912 --> 11:05.699
What if others get sick?
The group's survival comes first.

11:06.583 --> 11:08.699
Your medication
must be wearing off.

11:08.877 --> 11:10.333
The pain's making you say this.

11:10.503 --> 11:12.414
I'm not in pain.
I know exactly what I'm saying.

11:12.589 --> 11:14.500
If you weren't so selfish,
you'd understand.

11:14.674 --> 11:15.754
Hey. You can't leave.

11:15.925 --> 11:18.177
- Help! In the Sweetbriar, I need help!
- Hey.

11:18.344 --> 11:20.300
- Hunter, shut up. Do you wanna die?
- Yes!

11:20.471 --> 11:21.551
Help!

11:21.723 --> 11:24.089
- Get off! Help! Help!
- Stop!

11:24.267 --> 11:26.053
- Shut up.
- Let's look him in the freezer.

11:26.227 --> 11:27.603
[MUFFLED]

11:27.770 --> 11:29.681
NORRIE:
Shut up.

11:31.357 --> 11:35.475
I can't believe he's pissed
about us trying to save his life.

11:35.862 --> 11:38.899
Julia said
there's something inside of us.

11:39.407 --> 11:41.864
And it must be that
that's making him act like this.

11:43.161 --> 11:45.197
We're infected.

11:45.538 --> 11:47.324
Terrific.

11:50.960 --> 11:52.461
More giant-ass meteors?

11:53.004 --> 11:54.540
Secondary impacts.

11:54.714 --> 11:57.797
When debris from the first impact
comes raining back down.

11:57.967 --> 12:00.049
It's called ejecta.

12:02.222 --> 12:04.508
Or, you know,
maybe it's, you know, not that.

12:04.682 --> 12:08.846
So you're telling me
that those seizures that we had

12:09.020 --> 12:12.137
when we said
the pink stars are falling...

12:14.067 --> 12:17.980
meant that we were prophesying
the end of the world?

12:18.154 --> 12:23.274
Look, I probably have no idea
what I'm talking about.

12:30.875 --> 12:33.912
Even if we survive
whatever's infecting us,

12:34.087 --> 12:36.499
the whole world is gone.

12:38.424 --> 12:40.801
There's no future for us.

12:41.678 --> 12:44.511
We have nothing to look forward to.

12:46.808 --> 12:48.389
Maybe we should just join them.

12:48.977 --> 12:51.389
The kinship? No way.

12:51.562 --> 12:53.939
What's the point, Joe?

12:54.607 --> 12:59.397
This entire town was infected
in those cocoons.

13:00.154 --> 13:02.406
The kinship has won.

13:07.245 --> 13:09.327
No, it hasn't.

13:09.497 --> 13:11.658
We resisted.

13:11.833 --> 13:13.494
[BELL JINGLING]

13:14.002 --> 13:15.663
Stay down.

13:15.837 --> 13:16.917
Be quiet.

13:24.262 --> 13:25.297
Stay here.

13:32.854 --> 13:36.187
- Aah!
- Joe, stop! I'm not gonna hurt you.

13:38.860 --> 13:40.691
What are you two doing here?

13:40.862 --> 13:42.773
[BANGING ON DOOR
AND HUNTER YELLING]

13:43.364 --> 13:44.444
ls someone in there?

13:44.615 --> 13:46.992
- You're not taking him.
- Taking who?

13:47.577 --> 13:49.818
- What's going on?
- Did Junior and Eva send you?

13:50.913 --> 13:52.323
Are you a part of the kinship?

13:52.498 --> 13:55.365
No. Not after what they did to Abby,
and I take it from the fact

13:55.543 --> 13:58.250
that you have someone in the freezer,
you're not part of the kinship.

13:58.421 --> 13:59.831
JOE:
After everything you've done,

14:00.423 --> 14:02.288
why should we listen
to anything you say?

14:03.676 --> 14:05.257
Because I killed Christine.

14:08.681 --> 14:12.048
If Christine's dead,
does that mean the infection's gone?

14:13.061 --> 14:15.052
- I don't know.
- What infection?

14:15.980 --> 14:17.140
No way, Norrie.

14:17.315 --> 14:18.395
I still don't trust him.

14:18.566 --> 14:20.682
He killed Angie,
and now he's killed again.

14:20.860 --> 14:22.225
Joe.

14:23.321 --> 14:26.279
What Sam did to Angie
is unforgivable.

14:29.410 --> 14:31.787
But we're all fugitives
from the kinship.

14:34.290 --> 14:35.871
And there's not many of us.

14:40.088 --> 14:41.874
[MUFFLED]

14:42.048 --> 14:44.130
- Why is he gagged?
JOE: He wouldn't stop yelling.

14:44.300 --> 14:46.382
We took him from Eva.
She was trying to kill him.

14:46.552 --> 14:47.587
Which he said he wanted.

14:49.555 --> 14:50.590
I won't yell.

14:51.349 --> 14:52.885
I don't want them to find me.

14:55.436 --> 14:57.017
Thank you for saving my life.

15:00.274 --> 15:03.107
Looks like you broke a couple of ribs
during your fall as well.

15:03.277 --> 15:05.063
You'll heal,
but it's gonna take a while.

15:05.238 --> 15:07.024
We didn't bring any pain medication.

15:09.867 --> 15:12.984
Here.
This'll get you through a few hours.

15:16.541 --> 15:18.156
Do you remember what happened?

15:21.421 --> 15:24.629
Eva told me I was using up
too many resources.

15:25.341 --> 15:28.003
That it would be best if I died.

15:28.386 --> 15:29.501
I said, okay.

15:29.679 --> 15:31.795
What made you change your mind?

15:31.973 --> 15:33.759
I don't know. It's weird. I--

15:33.933 --> 15:37.221
I remember thinking
that all I cared about was the kinship.

15:38.396 --> 15:41.103
That felt more important
than my own life.

15:41.607 --> 15:43.222
But it doesn't now?

15:44.986 --> 15:47.102
I don't wanna die.

15:49.907 --> 15:52.364
It's good to have you back, Hunter.

15:53.119 --> 15:54.279
- Incoming.
SAM: The freezer.

15:54.454 --> 15:57.161
They won't look for you if they find me.
Go, go, go.

15:58.040 --> 16:00.031
[GRUNTING]

16:01.252 --> 16:02.833
JOE:
Hey. Hey.

16:03.004 --> 16:04.289
Why are you doing this?

16:04.464 --> 16:07.297
I can never make up for what I did
to you. But I can protect you,

16:07.467 --> 16:10.209
give you a chance to fight back
against whatever's happening to us.

16:10.386 --> 16:12.502
Whatever you hear, don't come out.

16:24.650 --> 16:25.901
[BANGING]

16:26.068 --> 16:27.148
All clear.

16:27.320 --> 16:28.560
[FREEZER OPENS]

16:31.240 --> 16:34.357
Told you they'd be gone.
I heard the door chime again.

16:34.535 --> 16:36.571
Who do you think was here?

16:36.746 --> 16:38.953
I don't know.
But Sam saved our asses.

16:40.500 --> 16:43.207
The sun rose. At least there's that.

16:43.377 --> 16:44.833
[HUNTER WHIMPERS]

16:46.464 --> 16:49.376
Hey. How you feeling?

16:49.550 --> 16:50.630
Any better?

16:52.803 --> 16:54.304
Hey.

16:54.472 --> 16:56.008
Drink this. It'll help.

16:59.018 --> 17:00.349
[NORRIE YELPS]

17:01.771 --> 17:05.104
You're keeping me from doing my duty
for the kinship.

17:05.274 --> 17:07.731
Take me back to Town Hall
or I'll scream.

17:07.902 --> 17:10.359
Yeah, and we'll put you back
in the freezer and gag you.

17:13.324 --> 17:17.784
- Why is he acting like this again?
- |-- I don't know.

17:18.579 --> 17:20.160
- Hunter, no!
- Hey, man--

17:20.331 --> 17:21.821
Get back! Stay back!

17:21.999 --> 17:24.376
- Calm down, Hunter.
- I swear, if you come any closer!

17:24.961 --> 17:26.576
You want me to calm down!

17:26.754 --> 17:28.710
You are keeping me
from doing my duty!

17:30.341 --> 17:31.672
[G RU NTS]

17:44.146 --> 17:45.522
Where are they going?

17:47.066 --> 17:49.978
I don't know. But look at them.

17:50.152 --> 17:51.767
They look like ants
marching in a line,

17:51.946 --> 17:54.779
doing whatever Queen Christine
ordered them to.

17:54.949 --> 17:59.909
Just a bunch Of mindless drones
only caring about her kinship.

18:00.079 --> 18:01.410
[JOE SIGHS]

18:03.124 --> 18:04.330
Don't let me get like that.

18:08.671 --> 18:10.832
We're in this together.

18:11.215 --> 18:14.753
All the way to the bitter,
apocalyptic end.

18:22.268 --> 18:24.725
I was thinking about Hunter.

18:25.354 --> 18:27.265
He got all Freaky Friday again

18:27.440 --> 18:30.432
right after Sam gave him
another one Of those pain pills.

18:30.610 --> 18:33.226
When he's in pain,
he's as normal as Hunter will ever be.

18:33.863 --> 18:38.152
But when he's on the meds,
he's like one Of those drones outside.

18:38.326 --> 18:39.736
HUNTER:
Joe. Norrie.

18:39.910 --> 18:43.528
Oh, God. Should we take bets
on which Hunter we're gonna get?

18:43.706 --> 18:45.913
Well, if it's drone boy,
we're screwed.

18:46.083 --> 18:48.995
Joe. Norrie. Please, help me.

18:49.462 --> 18:52.204
The pain is back. I'm scared.

18:52.381 --> 18:54.337
What the hell is going on with you?

18:54.508 --> 18:55.714
I think it's fear.

18:56.427 --> 18:58.213
What do you mean?

18:59.138 --> 19:02.676
When I was 8,
I was in a car accident with my mom.

19:05.311 --> 19:07.677
I was right there watching her die.

19:10.274 --> 19:13.892
I had no idea. I'm so sorry.

19:14.403 --> 19:19.113
Ever since,
my greatest fear is dying young.

19:20.284 --> 19:22.866
But my point is,

19:23.037 --> 19:25.949
after my fall I should have been
scared out Of my mind.

19:26.123 --> 19:29.240
But I didn't feel anything
because Of the pain meds.

19:29.919 --> 19:32.331
And then when the pills wear Off,

19:32.505 --> 19:34.291
I remember how afraid I am.

19:36.300 --> 19:38.006
And I'm me again.

19:43.516 --> 19:44.551
It's not the pain.

19:46.102 --> 19:48.184
It's the emotion.

19:49.855 --> 19:50.890
What do you mean?

19:51.565 --> 19:54.648
DO you remember
when Sam stood you up

19:54.819 --> 19:57.652
- and I lost it?
- Yeah.

19:57.822 --> 20:00.814
That's when you said
the real me was back.

20:01.659 --> 20:02.899
I was angry.

20:03.619 --> 20:06.986
Christine is trying to keep us
from having emotions,

20:07.164 --> 20:10.748
because when our feelings surface,
so does our humanity.

20:10.918 --> 20:12.533
For me it's anger,

20:12.712 --> 20:14.873
and for Hunter, it's fear.

20:15.047 --> 20:17.459
- What about me?
- Grief.

20:18.718 --> 20:20.333
Your sister.

20:20.511 --> 20:22.547
It was why Christine wanted you
to forgive Sam,

20:22.722 --> 20:24.678
so you could move on
and join the kinship.

20:26.559 --> 20:27.765
DO you know what this means?

20:29.103 --> 20:30.138
DO you?

20:32.189 --> 20:34.680
We have a way to fight back.

20:35.693 --> 20:37.775
A way to fight the kinship.

20:38.571 --> 20:41.313
Pack your stuff. As soon as the coast
is clear, we're leaving.

20:41.490 --> 20:42.650
Where are we going?

20:44.076 --> 20:46.112
TO find Julia.

20:50.541 --> 20:53.453
That damn meteor probably took out
half the country.

20:53.627 --> 20:56.209
[DOME CREAKING]

20:56.380 --> 20:59.338
We don't know if what happened
outside happened everywhere.

20:59.925 --> 21:01.461
We need to contact
the outside world.

21:01.635 --> 21:03.466
Oh, do we?

21:03.971 --> 21:05.552
What's knowing gonna do for you?

21:09.226 --> 21:11.683
You know, Jim, if you're just
gonna stand there being useless,

21:11.854 --> 21:14.641
why don't you do it outside
where you don't distract me?

21:16.233 --> 21:19.225
You're always Miss Can-DO, huh?

21:21.280 --> 21:22.645
Fine.

21:22.823 --> 21:25.064
I'm gonna look for my dog.

21:29.288 --> 21:31.028
Indy!

21:31.207 --> 21:33.163
Indy, where you at, boy?

21:34.126 --> 21:35.866
Indy.

21:57.858 --> 21:59.473
[KEYBOARD CLICKING]

22:02.822 --> 22:04.187
Change your mind? Care to help?

22:16.502 --> 22:17.537
Forget it.

22:18.838 --> 22:21.295
It's no use. There's, um...

22:23.217 --> 22:24.957
There's nothing left out there.

22:25.135 --> 22:26.420
How do you know that?

22:26.595 --> 22:28.711
See for yourself.

22:43.654 --> 22:45.315
You need to be doing this now?

22:45.489 --> 22:47.901
I knew the guy
who owned this house.

22:48.075 --> 22:49.690
Ferguson Faulkner.

22:49.869 --> 22:50.949
Don't think Old Ferg...

22:51.912 --> 22:54.153
would want his house
turned into a torture chamber.

22:55.833 --> 22:59.496
He was a, you know,
bleeding-heart type, rich as he was.

22:59.670 --> 23:03.037
And was a lush too.

23:05.509 --> 23:09.843
Which means,
we get to watch the world end

23:10.014 --> 23:12.926
while we drink the good stuff.

23:13.100 --> 23:14.510
[JIM SIGHS]

23:15.019 --> 23:17.852
Obviously, he was a bird lover tOO.

23:18.314 --> 23:21.431
Loved them so much,
he had them killed and stuffed.

23:21.609 --> 23:23.645
[LAUGHS]

23:23.819 --> 23:25.434
- Something funny?
- I wasjust thinking

23:25.613 --> 23:28.571
of how good I'd look
stuffed up there.

23:28.741 --> 23:30.652
They'd have a hard time
with your hair, though.

23:30.826 --> 23:32.362
And no trouble at all with yours.

23:32.536 --> 23:33.616
Well, that's true.

23:34.788 --> 23:36.369
Remember that time everything froze?

23:37.166 --> 23:39.407
Yeah. That was the night Barbie--

23:40.336 --> 23:42.122
Barbie what?

23:45.382 --> 23:47.122
Nothing. Never mind.

23:47.301 --> 23:51.214
GO on with your fascinating story.

23:51.388 --> 23:56.599
Well, when I fished Lyle Chumley
out Of the lake, and, um...

23:56.769 --> 23:59.306
Sidebar, should never do that again.
Heh-heh.

23:59.480 --> 24:01.471
He started talking
about the end Of days

24:01.649 --> 24:03.480
and how the world would be on fire

24:03.651 --> 24:07.064
and some, you know,
wall of flame a thousand feet high.

24:07.237 --> 24:12.197
Pfft. Like a lot of things,
he got the apocalypse wrong tOO.

24:16.163 --> 24:17.619
The sixth extinction.

24:18.499 --> 24:21.286
- What?
- Dinosaurs were the fifth extinction.

24:21.877 --> 24:23.708
Big Old asteroid came,

24:23.879 --> 24:26.541
bye-bye, triceratops,
bye-bye, brontosaurus.

24:26.715 --> 24:29.457
We, humans, will be the sixth.

24:29.969 --> 24:32.551
Well, we may be
an endangered species,

24:32.721 --> 24:35.679
but we're not going the way
of the dOdO any time soon.

24:36.642 --> 24:37.677
NO?

24:40.396 --> 24:43.229
Say this fishbowl doesn't crack,

24:43.399 --> 24:44.889
how long you think it's gonna be

24:45.067 --> 24:47.274
before Christine comes looking
to wipe us out?

24:47.444 --> 24:50.060
She said we stay out Of her way,
she'll stay out Of ours.

24:50.239 --> 24:53.606
Was that before or after
you sold her out and I tried to kill her?

24:54.368 --> 24:56.734
I say-- Ungh.

24:57.955 --> 25:00.162
--instead Of getting wiped out,

25:04.211 --> 25:06.497
maybe we should do the wiping.

25:07.172 --> 25:08.548
There's no point.

25:08.716 --> 25:11.173
What, you afraid of getting
your hands dirty?

25:12.845 --> 25:14.210
It's not about that.

25:14.388 --> 25:16.754
There's too many of them.

25:17.349 --> 25:20.466
You and I are not much
of a resistance.

25:20.644 --> 25:22.680
Not without a way
to turn people back.

25:22.855 --> 25:24.811
Listen, I say we take these,

25:24.982 --> 25:29.646
we take out as many Of those, uh,
body snatchers as we can.

25:30.195 --> 25:32.686
You know, we make a last stand,
like Butch and Sundance.

25:32.865 --> 25:34.856
Including the part where they die?

25:35.534 --> 25:38.196
See, that's what you
never understood.

25:39.288 --> 25:40.698
Since the dome came down,

25:40.873 --> 25:43.580
that was the only outcome
there was ever gonna be.

25:46.295 --> 25:47.330
You're right.

25:47.963 --> 25:49.464
I can't believe I'm gonna say it,

25:51.800 --> 25:53.665
but you were right.

25:57.514 --> 26:00.722
Well, finally happened, huh?

26:01.143 --> 26:07.480
You finally, uh, given up on all that
sunny-side-up Pollyanna routine,

26:08.442 --> 26:11.855
talking all that crap about
how the dome was here to save us.

26:12.029 --> 26:14.691
Oh, no, I wasn't wrong.

26:14.865 --> 26:16.730
NO, the dome's here to protect.

26:24.041 --> 26:27.033
It's just not here to protect us.

26:35.260 --> 26:39.003
Guess this means
I'll never get to go to Paris.

26:40.182 --> 26:41.922
Pads?

26:43.185 --> 26:49.647
Plenty of stuff to regret more
than not getting to that dirty ciudad.

26:49.817 --> 26:51.933
That's Spanish.

26:54.613 --> 26:58.231
I was surprised
that, uh, you never made it there,

26:58.408 --> 27:03.072
being all cosmopolitan like you are.

27:03.580 --> 27:07.038
Surprised someone like you
ended up here in Chester's Mill,

27:07.209 --> 27:08.745
to be honest.

27:08.919 --> 27:10.329
How'd that happen?

27:10.504 --> 27:12.711
- Peter Shumway.
- Right.

27:14.383 --> 27:16.214
You know, I gotta tell you,

27:16.385 --> 27:19.001
never made sense to me,
the two Of you.

27:19.179 --> 27:21.295
Now you tell me.

27:23.392 --> 27:25.633
I don't know.

27:26.770 --> 27:29.853
He was a doctor.
Maybe I was looking for security.

27:30.023 --> 27:31.058
Find it?

27:33.110 --> 27:35.442
You know, he was a mess.

27:36.822 --> 27:38.778
Couldn't even take care Of himself.

27:39.741 --> 27:42.153
I never knew what it felt like
to be safe or in love

27:42.327 --> 27:43.863
until I met Barbie.

27:44.037 --> 27:45.823
Yeah, look at how that worked out.

27:51.795 --> 27:53.080
[SCOFFS]

27:54.715 --> 27:56.751
Such a cliche, right?

27:57.593 --> 28:01.711
Fall for the dark, mysterious guy, ahem,
and then get all bent out Of shape

28:01.889 --> 28:04.380
when he turns out
to be dark and mysterious.

28:06.560 --> 28:10.849
Look at us, two former enemies
drinking at the end of the world.

28:11.023 --> 28:12.183
Former?

28:12.357 --> 28:14.848
Oh, come on, Jim.

28:15.360 --> 28:17.851
You must have regrets.

28:19.698 --> 28:21.484
Yeah, Of course I do.

28:22.367 --> 28:24.198
With Junior.

28:27.039 --> 28:30.156
Pushed him too hard, I suppose.

28:30.584 --> 28:31.994
Talk about a cliche.

28:32.961 --> 28:36.795
Treat your son like a second chance
to overcome your own shortcomings,

28:36.965 --> 28:38.956
instead Of treating him
like his own person.

28:39.134 --> 28:42.547
You named him after yourself,
for God's sake.

28:43.180 --> 28:44.386
You're wrong.

28:45.057 --> 28:46.467
Nice try.

28:46.642 --> 28:50.180
You know, you and me, we may have
some stuff in common, Julia,

28:50.354 --> 28:54.472
but do not try to dissect me
with your cheapjack psychobabble.

28:55.567 --> 28:59.025
There's only one thing in this life
that I regret

28:59.196 --> 29:01.107
and that's letting everything
that I earned,

29:01.281 --> 29:03.943
everything I ever cared about,

29:05.118 --> 29:07.370
get taken away from me.

29:08.830 --> 29:12.869
And I'll be damned if! let anything
get taken away again.

29:25.806 --> 29:27.216
[DOG BARKING]

29:30.352 --> 29:32.092
Indy!

29:39.111 --> 29:41.147
There you are, boy.
There you are, boy.

29:43.115 --> 29:44.355
Good boy.

29:46.994 --> 29:48.985
Oh, yeah.

29:49.162 --> 29:52.154
Where were you? Where were you?

29:56.211 --> 29:57.246
Is that the sun?

29:58.297 --> 30:00.754
NO. It's coming
from the wrong direction.

30:04.344 --> 30:06.300
JULIA:
It's getting closer. What is it?

30:06.471 --> 30:08.757
It's a wall Of flame.

30:23.322 --> 30:24.903
I'm gonna bring back Sam.

30:26.033 --> 30:27.273
Just like you asked.

31:01.193 --> 31:02.808
[BELL JINGLING]

31:14.247 --> 31:15.953
Whoa, stop!

31:16.792 --> 31:18.453
Joe, I'm not gonna hurt you.

31:19.211 --> 31:21.418
What are you two doing here?

31:22.923 --> 31:24.538
Audrey.

31:27.719 --> 31:29.459
- Have you seen Sam?
- We have.

31:29.638 --> 31:30.673
Where?

31:32.265 --> 31:34.221
The Sweetbriar.

31:40.232 --> 31:42.348
Whatever you hear, don't come out.

31:43.527 --> 31:44.562
[BELL JINGLES]

31:51.243 --> 31:52.278
Sam?

31:53.286 --> 31:54.412
You in here?

32:00.836 --> 32:03.202
Junior. Hey.

32:04.506 --> 32:06.371
It's good to see you.

32:06.758 --> 32:07.793
What are you doing in here?

32:10.095 --> 32:12.211
When those pink stars hit,
I took cover.

32:13.723 --> 32:14.758
Have they stopped?

32:16.101 --> 32:17.637
For now.

32:17.811 --> 32:19.927
Junior, why is their blood
on your hands?

32:20.105 --> 32:21.936
It's Christine.

32:23.483 --> 32:24.643
She's been stabbed.

32:26.069 --> 32:27.855
She's alive.

32:29.072 --> 32:31.233
But you're the only one I can trust.

32:31.825 --> 32:33.440
DO you know who did this?

32:34.244 --> 32:35.825
NO.

32:37.164 --> 32:40.372
- But I took her body to the caves.
- The caves?

32:41.168 --> 32:43.033
I stopped the bleeding
the best that I could.

32:43.211 --> 32:45.327
But you have to help her.

32:47.716 --> 32:49.581
Christine needs you, Sam.

32:50.302 --> 32:52.008
Lead the way.

32:58.685 --> 33:01.051
SAM:
My God. The dust is so thick.

33:02.731 --> 33:05.393
- You can't even see the sun.
- It's like it was before.

33:07.903 --> 33:09.609
You don't remember?

33:09.779 --> 33:12.395
Remember? Remember what?

33:13.950 --> 33:15.656
The Great Destruction.

33:15.827 --> 33:17.283
It's happening all over again.

33:17.913 --> 33:20.279
Like it did on our home world.

33:22.042 --> 33:23.578
It was so long ago.

33:24.503 --> 33:25.913
So many lives lost.

33:26.087 --> 33:28.578
- Which is why we traveled so far.
- For safety.

33:30.675 --> 33:32.051
Is it coming back to you now?

33:32.219 --> 33:33.755
Of course.

33:37.098 --> 33:39.259
All these people,
aren't you worried anyone out here

33:39.434 --> 33:41.390
could be the one
who stabbed Christine?

33:41.561 --> 33:43.472
JUNIOR:
They won't follow us in the caves.

33:43.980 --> 33:46.016
They aren't special like you and I.

33:46.191 --> 33:48.147
And Eva. Barbie.

33:49.069 --> 33:51.776
Each of us has a unique purpose.

33:51.947 --> 33:54.063
That's what separates us
from the drones.

33:54.491 --> 33:57.983
And right now our purpose
is to save our queen.

34:11.007 --> 34:13.623
- Watch your step.
- Thanks.

34:13.802 --> 34:16.544
You're no good to us
if you fall and break your neck.

34:16.721 --> 34:19.383
You never said why you brought
Christine down here.

34:19.558 --> 34:20.764
That's what she asked me to do.

34:21.601 --> 34:24.217
You spoke to Christine?
She's conscious?

34:25.397 --> 34:26.728
You'll see.

34:26.898 --> 34:28.684
We're almost there.

34:32.862 --> 34:34.898
Come on. Keep up.

34:44.457 --> 34:45.913
Junior, slow down.

34:46.084 --> 34:47.824
Can't keep Christine waiting.

34:51.840 --> 34:53.501
Junior.

34:53.675 --> 34:55.506
Junior. Ungh!

34:55.677 --> 34:56.757
What are you doing?

34:56.928 --> 34:59.010
I'm hurting you,
like you hurt Christine.

35:01.266 --> 35:03.302
I had no choice. She's evil.

35:03.476 --> 35:05.762
You're still not one of us.
Not part Of the group.

35:08.023 --> 35:11.311
DO you know what happens to those
that aren't part Of the group?

35:12.110 --> 35:13.350
You don't understand.

35:13.528 --> 35:16.019
- She put something in us.
- I know.

35:19.951 --> 35:21.327
We have to stop her.

35:21.494 --> 35:24.486
The only one who needs
to be stopped is you.

35:56.780 --> 35:58.862
Oh, my God.

36:00.158 --> 36:03.116
Oh, my God. NO.

36:18.677 --> 36:20.963
[INAUDIBLE]

36:24.724 --> 36:27.466
NO. NO!

36:27.936 --> 36:29.221
Hey, stop.

36:30.980 --> 36:32.356
I can help you! There's a way in!

36:32.941 --> 36:34.021
There's a way in here!

36:34.192 --> 36:36.308
EVA:
Dale, you can't help them.

36:46.413 --> 36:48.495
The world outside, it's the past.

36:48.915 --> 36:50.906
Humanity, with all its terrible flaws,

36:51.084 --> 36:53.951
with all the mistakes it's made,
it's gone.

36:54.587 --> 36:56.418
If we're gonna survive,

36:56.589 --> 36:57.999
you have to let it go.

36:59.259 --> 37:01.420
I don't think I can.

37:06.307 --> 37:07.843
Dale.

37:08.351 --> 37:10.683
When are you gonna admit
to what you already know?

37:10.854 --> 37:12.640
You're one Of us.

37:14.023 --> 37:17.891
You and I,
we're part of something greater.

37:23.908 --> 37:25.944
Julia gave this back to me.

37:32.292 --> 37:35.830
They're part Of a world
you used to be a part of.

37:36.004 --> 37:37.335
But you can't save that world.

37:39.758 --> 37:42.170
You can save the one
you're part Of now.

37:46.389 --> 37:48.300
The one right here.

37:49.851 --> 37:51.091
Please, Dale.

37:51.269 --> 37:52.304
Join us.

37:53.480 --> 37:55.186
Save us.

38:35.188 --> 38:37.179
Christine's in there.

38:37.357 --> 38:39.222
Because Of you.

38:40.151 --> 38:43.518
When she comes out,
you're gonna answer for what you did.

38:48.159 --> 38:52.903
Safe to say your Eiffel Tower's
a puddle Of molten iron.

38:53.081 --> 38:55.197
We're all that's left.

38:55.375 --> 38:57.707
You and me, Jim.

38:57.877 --> 39:01.995
We're the last living humans
on Earth.

39:04.092 --> 39:05.548
[LAUGHING]

39:11.850 --> 39:16.640
We're the last living humans
on Earth.

39:19.023 --> 39:20.604
[BARKING]

39:30.326 --> 39:31.827
Norrie! Joe! They're Okay.

39:32.954 --> 39:35.366
- What are you doing here?
- We came to find you.

39:36.666 --> 39:37.746
Hunter. But he's--

39:37.917 --> 39:39.077
He's one of us.

39:40.295 --> 39:41.831
Just recently converted.

39:44.591 --> 39:46.172
There's a way to save the town.

39:47.510 --> 39:48.545
How?

39:49.721 --> 39:51.336
Emotion.

39:57.395 --> 40:00.353
Oh, no, no, no.
You're not going anywhere.

40:00.982 --> 40:03.564
Are you ready to face judgment?

40:05.695 --> 40:08.607
You're all sure you wanna do this?

40:09.490 --> 40:12.197
Like you even need to ask, Red.

40:14.787 --> 40:16.072
Hell yeah, I do.

40:16.581 --> 40:18.037
Okay.

40:19.334 --> 40:21.245
Then the resistance starts here.

40:36.684 --> 40:38.220
[BEEPING]

40:39.020 --> 40:40.510
WOMAN [OVER COMM]:
Is anyone there?

40:40.688 --> 40:42.064
Please conﬁrm.

40:42.231 --> 40:44.813
I repeat. Is anyone there?

40:44.984 --> 40:47.225
Please conﬁrm.
